<title>USA: Hughes CEO sees consolidations nearing end.</title>
<headline>Hughes CEO sees consolidations nearing end.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hughes Electronics Corp chief executive Michael Armstrong said Thursday he believes consolidation among major players in the defense industry is coming to a close.</p>
<p>&quot;I think we're at the end of major consolidation,&quot; Armstrong said at a news conference announcing a merger between Hughes Aircraft and Raytheon Co.</p>
<p>He noted some of the industry's smaller players may likely be swept up in future consolidation or will be forced to stay in niche markets.</p>
<p>The U.S. defense industry has been consolidating at a rapid pace in recent years, primarily due to a decline in government defense spending.</p>
<p>((-- Robin Sidel, New York newsdesk 212 859-1610))</p>
